# Podman and Containers

This file contains Podman and container notes useful for RHCSA and Linux administration.

## 1. What is Podman?

Podman is a container engine used in RHEL-based systems.

Containers are isolated environments used to run applications.

Podman is similar to Docker but:
- daemonless
- rootless support
- better integration with systemd
- used in RHCSA/RHCE

## 2. Basic Container Concepts

Important terms:

```text
Image      = template
Container  = running instance of image
Registry   = image repository
```

Flow:

```text
Image -> Container -> Running Application
```

## 3. Install Podman

```bash
dnf install podman -y
```

Verify:

```bash
podman --version
```

## 4. Search Images

Search image:

```bash
podman search nginx
```

## 5. Pull Images

Download image:

```bash
podman pull nginx
```

View local images:

```bash
podman images
```

## 6. Run Containers

Run nginx container:

```bash
podman run -d nginx
```

Explanation:

```text
-d = detached mode
```

Run container with custom name:

```bash
podman run -d --name web nginx
```

## 7. List Containers

Show running containers:

```bash
podman ps
```

Show all containers:

```bash
podman ps -a
```

## 8. Stop and Remove Containers

Stop container:

```bash
podman stop web
```

Start container:

```bash
podman start web
```

Restart container:

```bash
podman restart web
```

Remove container:

```bash
podman rm web
```

Force remove:

```bash
podman rm -f web
```

## 9. Container Ports

Expose port:

```bash
podman run -d -p 8080:80 nginx
```

Explanation:

```text
HOST_PORT:CONTAINER_PORT
```

Verify:

```bash
ss -tulpn
```

Access website:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8080
```

## 10. Container Logs

View logs:

```bash
podman logs web
```

Follow logs:

```bash
podman logs -f web
```

## 11. Execute Commands Inside Container

Open shell:

```bash
podman exec -it web bash
```

Explanation:

```text
-i = interactive
-t = terminal
```

## 12. Volumes

Mount host directory:

```bash
podman run -d -v /web:/usr/share/nginx/html nginx
```

Explanation:

```text
Host directory is mounted inside container.
```

## 13. SELinux and Containers

If SELinux blocks volume access:

```bash
podman run -d -v /web:/usr/share/nginx/html:Z nginx
```

Explanation:

```text
:Z adjusts SELinux labels for containers.
```

## 14. Generate systemd Service

Generate service file:

```bash
podman generate systemd --name web
```

Save service:

```bash
podman generate systemd --name web > /etc/systemd/system/web.service
```

Reload systemd:

```bash
systemctl daemon-reload
```

Enable service:

```bash
systemctl enable web.service
```

## 15. Rootless Containers

Run as normal user:

```bash
podman run -d nginx
```

Benefits:

- better security
- no root required

## 16. Remove Images

Remove image:

```bash
podman rmi nginx
```

Remove unused data:

```bash
podman system prune
```

## 17. Troubleshooting

Check running containers:

```bash
podman ps
```

Check logs:

```bash
podman logs web
```

Check ports:

```bash
ss -tulpn
```

Check firewall:

```bash
firewall-cmd --list-all
```

Check SELinux:

```bash
ausearch -m AVC -ts recent
```

## 18. Example Troubleshooting

Problem:

```text
Container website is not accessible.
```

Check container:

```bash
podman ps
```

Check exposed ports:

```bash
podman ps
```

Check listening ports:

```bash
ss -tulpn | grep 8080
```

Check firewall:

```bash
firewall-cmd --list-all
```

Check SELinux:

```bash
ausearch -m AVC -ts recent
```

